info: usu. after -masu stem of verb; read as ごこち

english_definitions: bare earth (i.e. ground not covered by a roof)
path through a gate (or through a garden, etc.)
something that seems fine at first but turns out to be very bad (e.g. product, business)
the earth (historically, esp. as opposed to the heavens)
(period of) refraining from construction in the direction of the god of the earth (in Onmyōdō)
info: also written as 犯土, 椎, 槌
